  "prompt": "What are some publicly listed solar companies in India?",
  "response": "There are several publicly listed solar companies in India that are involved in various aspects of the solar energy sector, including manufacturing, installation, and project development. Here are some notable ones:\n\n1. **Tata Power Solar Systems Ltd**\n   - **Ticker Symbol**: TATAPOWER\n   - **Description**: A subsidiary of Tata Power, it is one of the largest solar companies in India, involved in solar cell and module manufacturing, EPC (Engineering, Procurement, and Construction) services, and solar power project development.\n\n2. **Vikram Solar Ltd**\n   - **Ticker Symbol**: VIKRAMSOL\n   - **Description**: A leading solar energy solutions provider, Vikram Solar is engaged in the manufacturing of PV modules, and also provides EPC services and develops solar power projects.\n\n3. **Adani Green Energy Ltd**\n   - **Ticker Symbol**: ADANIGREEN\n   - **Description**: A part of the Adani Group, Adani Green Energy focuses on renewable energy projects, including solar, wind, and hybrid power plants.\n\n4. **Waaree Energies Ltd**\n   - **Ticker Symbol**: WAAREERT\n   - **Description**: Waaree Energies is one of India\u2019s leading solar module manufacturers and also provides EPC services and solar project development.\n\n5. **Azure Power Global Ltd**\n   - **Ticker Symbol**: AZRE\n   - **Description**: Azure Power is involved in the development, construction, ownership, and operation of solar power plants in India.\n\n6. **Sterling and Wilson Renewable Energy Ltd**\n   - **Ticker Symbol**: SWSOLAR\n   - **Description**: A major player in the EPC sector, Sterling and Wilson focuses on solar and renewable energy projects.\n\nThese companies can be found listed on stock exchanges like the National Stock Exchange of India (NSE) and the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE). It's always a good idea to check the latest information and financial performance of these companies before making any investment decisions.",
